<div class="penelope">
  <img src="/img/welcomingcat.png" alt="Penelope the Neocities cat">
  <div class="penelope-Bubble">
    <p>Looking good! But every great page needs a big title at the top &mdash; something that says <em>this is MY website</em>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Headings give your page structure, like chapter titles in a book. The tag for the biggest, most important heading is <code><%= '<h1>' %></code>:</p>

<pre><code class="html"><%= '<h1>My Website</h1>' %></code></pre>

<p>It works exactly like the paragraph tag &mdash; an opening tag, your words, and a closing tag with a slash. HTML actually has six heading sizes, from <code><%= '<h1>' %></code> (the biggest) down to <code><%= '<h6>' %></code> (the smallest).</p>

<div class="your-Turn">
  <h4><i class="fa fa-pencil" aria-hidden="true"></i> Your turn</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>At the top of your page &mdash; just after the <code><%= '<body>' %></code> line, above your paragraphs &mdash; add a heading with a name for your site: <code><%= '<h1>My Website</h1>' %></code></li>
    <li>Make the words your own! <em>Sam's Corner</em>, <em>The Mushroom Zone</em>, whatever fits.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Check My Work</strong>.</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="bonus-Box">
  <h4>Heading rules of thumb</h4>
  <p>Use just one <code><%= '<h1>' %></code> per page &mdash; it's the main title. If you add sections later, give them <code><%= '<h2>' %></code> headings, then <code><%= '<h3>' %></code> inside those, and so on. We'll use an <code><%= '<h2>' %></code> in a few steps.</p>
</div>

<script>
  function lessonCheck(doc, html) {
    var headings = doc.querySelectorAll('body h1')

    if(headings.length == 0)
      return {ok: false, message: 'I don&rsquo;t see an ' + codeSample('<h1>') + ' heading yet. Add one above your paragraphs, like ' + codeSample('<h1>My Website</h1>') + '.'}

    if(missingClosingTag(html, 'h1'))
      return {ok: false, message: 'Your heading is missing its closing ' + codeSample('</h1>') + ' tag. Without it, the browser thinks the whole page is one giant heading!'}

    if(headings[0].textContent.trim() == '')
      return {ok: false, message: 'Your heading is empty! Put your site&rsquo;s name between ' + codeSample('<h1>') + ' and ' + codeSample('</h1>') + '.'}

    return {ok: true, message: 'A page with a proper title &mdash; nice heading!'}
  }
</script>
